  "prompt": "How much do psychologists charge for a cognitive behavioural therapy?",
  "response": "The cost of cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT) can vary widely depending on several factors, including the psychologist's qualifications and location, the duration and frequency of sessions, and whether the therapy is private or covered by insurance.\n\nIn the United States, for example, private CBT sessions typically range from $100 to $250 per hour. Some therapists offer sliding scale fees based on a patient's income, which can lower the cost. Additionally, therapy might be covered by health insurance, potentially reducing out-of-pocket expenses significantly.\n\nIn other countries, costs can differ. In the UK, private CBT sessions can range from \u00a340 to \u00a3100 per hour. In Australia, prices can range from AUD $120 to $250 per hour, but Medicare may cover a portion of the cost.\n\nIt's important to check with individual therapists and insurance providers for precise and current rates.",
